                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00 Nanking/77: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-04-15T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 15, 1927—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>164. Lockhart’s 17 to Legation, April 14, 3 p.m. For the present Department will
                    make no public comment with regard to note and would desire that Legation make
                    no public comment in Peking. Please cable us your comments and also information
                    as to any textual differences in the replies made by Eugene Chen to the several
                    Powers as well as the reaction in Peking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
